<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paper Moon (Channel 11 Sunday at 4 p.m.): Peter Bogdanovich's delightful 
Depression-era comedy, with Ryan O'Neal as a con man who latches on to a 
smart-alecky -- and Oscar-winning Tatum O'Neal. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Gigi (Channel 13 Monday at 11:30 a.m.): Vincente Minnelli's elegant belle 
epoque musical, written by Lerner and Loewe and starring Leslie Caron as 
Colette's young heroine, being groomed as a grand courtesan. (2:30) 
</P>
<P>
Klondike Annie (Channel 5 Friday at 4 a.m.): Vintage Mae West, in which she's 
on the lam in Alaska posing as an evangelist. Co-starring Victor McLaglen, whom 
she tells, "You're no earl paintin,' but you're a fascinatin' monster." (1:30) 
</P>
<P>
Under Capricorn (Channel 11 Saturday at 3 a.m.): Highly experimental and moody 
Hitchcock period piece, set in Australia and starring Ingrid Bergman and Joseph 
Cotten. (2:30) 
</P>
</TEXT>
