<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With television continuing to use actual news events as a source of 
inspiration, real-life incidents invariably turn up as the subjects of new 
productions. 
</P>
<P>
The latest example is "Tailspin: Behind the Korean Airliner Tragedy," a 
90-minute "HBO Showcase" drama airing Sunday at 9 p.m. on cable's Home Box 
Office. 
</P>
<P>
"Tailspin" tells about the Korean passenger jet shot down by a Soviet fighter 
plane after straying into Soviet airspace during the summer of 1983, resulting 
in the deaths of all 269 people aboard, including 66 Americans. 
</P>
<P>
It also focuses on the political turmoil that took place in Washington in 
response to the international incident. 
</P>
<P>
The cast includes Michael Moriarty, Michael Murphy, Chris Sarandon and Harris 
Yulin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
