104 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<TEXT>
<P>
Why is it when there finally comes a program that has some substance to it and 
it is meaty and grown-up that it is pulled from the airwaves? I am referring to 
"Heartbeat." It was a great program, along with others that have been pulled 
before they are given a fair chance. I don't know who is polled or what their 
mentality is, but give us a break, and no more sitcoms that need the brain of 
an insect to enjoy. Let's be real. Give us something worth turning on the 
television. "Heartbeat," "A Year in the Life," "Our House" and so many others 
have been given the round file. Good grief. 
</P>
<P>
Toni Jacobson, Monterey Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
