<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAKING WAVES OVER A SEA STORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is unfathomable that Fox threw $43 million in the drink to produce "The 
Abyss" ("Fox Plunges Into 'The Abyss' "). 
</P>
<P>
The tale of a submersible extraterrestrial spacecraft setting up a bivouac in 
Davy Jones' locker has already been filmed twice, in two excellent, albeit 
relatively inexpensive, renditions: "The Atomic Submarine" (1959) and 
"Destination Inner Space" (1966). 
</P>
<P>
Both of these versions were marked by imaginative scripting, solid acting and 
fairly decent special effects, especially considering their skeletal budgets. 
</P>
<P>
Why the need for an updated albatross that seems doomed to sink at the box 
office? 
</P>
<P>
FRANKLIN R. RUEHL 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
