<LENGTH>
<P>
83 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ADS AT THE MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After recently moving from Jacksonville, N.C., where movie tickets cost $4.50, 
I was shocked by the prices here -- $6 to $7. But what disturbs me the most 
about Los Angeles-area theaters is that many show commercials. If I wanted to 
see commercials I would stay home and watch TV, without buying any ticket. 
</P>
<P>
A final note: The commercial I see the most is an obnoxious one that makes no 
sense. Only at the end do we find out who it is for -- the L.A. Times. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT A. SCARPATO 
</P>
<P>
Westlake Village 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
