<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MATURE TRAVELER: CATCHING UP WITH KIWI ON NEW ZEALAND FARM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HANK KOVELL, Kovell is a veteran journalist in seniors' interests. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A New Zealand tour especially tailored for mature travelers is being offered 
for two departure dates this fall, Sept. 6 and 20. 
</P>
<P>
The 18-day tour begins in Auckland and proceeds to the Rotorua thermal area by 
way of Waitomo and the glowworm caves. The night is spent with a farm family to 
better acquaint the traveler with the kiwis, as the local people sometimes are 
called. 
</P>
<P>
The tour also visits the capital city of Wellington, then goes by ferry to 
South Island, where a train is boarded for a trip to historic Christchurch. 
</P>
<P>
Then it's through the Southern Alps via the Tranz Alpine Express, with a day 
viewing glaciers and taking a lake cruise, plus a visit to Milford Sound. 
</P>
<P>
Two free days for relaxation and exploring are next at Queenstown, where one 
may visit the national parks and the plentiful lakes and fiords. The trip ends 
at the handsome Victorian city of Dunedin. 
</P>
<P>
The tour is priced at $2,330 per person, which includes round-trip air from 
California via Air New Zealand, baggage assistance and transfers. Meals are not 
included, except for the farm-stay dinner and lunch on the Milford Sound 
cruise. The trip is planned for seniors over age 55 or members of AARP. 
</P>
<P>
For a complete itinerary, call toll-free (800) 228-8727 or (818) 707-0184. Or 
write to Baird Reynolds Ltd., 30315 Canwood St., No. 10, Agoura Hills, Calif. 
91301. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
Poole Tours is offering four trips for the senior adult during the holiday 
season. 
</P>
<P>
"Thanksgiving in the Valley of the Sun" departs Nov. 20. It's a four-night, 
five-day tour to the Phoenix area, including stops in Sedona, Oak Creek Canyon, 
Scottsdale, Paradise Valley and Rawhide. 
</P>
<P>
Travel is via Greyhound bus. The tour includes accommodations and four 
breakfasts and four dinners, including Thanksgiving dinner at the elegant 
Arizona Biltmore Hotel. Tour price is $519 per person. 
</P>
<P>
"Christmas in Victoria" departs Dec. 21, with two days in Vancouver, including 
a city tour and an evening tour with dinner. Then it's by ferry to Victoria for 
four days of sightseeing via motor coach and a festive Christmas dinner. 
</P>
<P>
All breakfasts and dinners in Victoria are included, as well as hotel 
accommodations. The price of $1,459 per person includes round-trip air 
transportation from Southern California and all sightseeing. 
</P>
<P>
"Christmas Luminarias" is the traditional festival of the lights in 
Albuquerque, N.M. The eight-day trip, which departs Dec. 21, includes Greyhound 
motor coach, welcome party, Christmas dinner and all accommodations and 
sightseeing. Stops on the itinerary include Sedona, Phoenix, Flagstaff, Las 
Cruces and the Petrified Forest. The per-person price is $689. 
</P>
<P>
A "San Antonio Christmas" takes you to that Texas city by air. Then you'll 
cruise the famed Riverwalk and tour the city. The package includes seven nights 
at the Hilton Palacio del Rio, plus two lunches and four dinners, including a 
Christmas dinner. Tour price is $1,049 per person, complete. 
</P>
<P>
For more comprehensive itinerary descriptions and other information, write to 
Poole Tours, P.O. Box 990, Temple City, Calif. 91780, or call (213) 283-3412, 
(818) 285-9775 or (714) 855-4918. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
Another popular senior group offering a variety of trips is Golden Tours, based 
in Alhambra. They offer a continuing program of travel, from one-day local 
theater or visitor attraction tours to regional trips in Southern California, 
plus trips to Canada, Mexico, Europe and Asia, and voyages by cruise ship. 
</P>
<P>
Day-trips usually include motor-coach transportation, sightseeing and lunch, 
dinner, the theater, shopping or local attractions in nearby places such as 
Santa Barbara, San Diego, Newport Beach, Lake Arrowhead, Marina del Rey, Ojai 
Valley, the Channel Islands, Catalina, Long Beach and the Queen Mary, Lawrence 
Welk Village in Escondido and Tijuana. 
</P>
<P>
Regional trips may run from one to four nights and include such popular 
destinations as Las Vegas, Laughlin, Reno, Yosemite, Death Valley, Grand 
Canyon, San Francisco, Phoenix, Tucson and Lake Tahoe. 
</P>
<P>
For those looking for deluxe tours and cruises to distant destinations, a large 
selection is offered, including air and motor-coach tours to Canada, the 
Ozarks, Florida, fall foliage tours in the northeastern United States or 
eastern Canada, plus Hawaii, Australia and New Zealand, or cruises to the 
Mediterranean and the Mexican Riviera. 
</P>
<P>
Holiday tours are also available for Thanksgiving, Christmas and New Year's. 
</P>
<P>
Golden Tours is a nonprofit membership corporation for travelers over the age 
of 50. It issues a monthly eight-page bulletin filled with listings of all 
available tours, including 30 or more day-tours and three pages of national and 
international tours and cruises. 
</P>
<P>
For day trips, free parking is available at two parking lots in Alhambra and 
Pasadena, where buses are boarded. 
</P>
<P>
Membership is $5. Contact Golden Tours, Box 1070, Alhambra 91802, (213) 
283-7876 or (818) 289-6271. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
A seasonal discount fare for mature travelers is being offered by Air Canada 
under the name "Freedom Flyer." Travelers from Los Angeles can fly non-stop to 
Toronto or Calgary, and from those cities connect with 26 major cities across 
Canada. 
</P>
<P>
Travelers must be at least 62 years old, and may bring a companion of any age 
for the same fare, providing they go to the same destination. 
</P>
<P>
There are three Freedom Flyer fares for flights that originate in the United 
States: $499, which allows stopovers at four destinations; $599 for one trip 
with 5 to 8 destinations and $699 for one trip with nine to 12 destinations. 
</P>
<P>
Travel must occur between Sept. 12 and Dec. 12. 
</P>
<P>
For information and reservations, contact a travel agent or call Air Canada 
toll-free at (800) 422-6232. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
Due to an error in editing, a recent item in this column on hotel discounts in 
Honolulu incorrectly referred to the Ala Moana Hotel. The hotel's correct name 
is the Moana Hotel. For information, call toll-free (800) 325-3535. 
</P>
</TEXT>
