<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIREFIGHTER PRAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
My home was one that survived the Puente Hills fire July 3. I returned home 
that evening to find it had been saved from total loss by a fine group of brave 
young men from Camp Paige. I watched them and they were determined not to give 
up. I still have a home, and I'm filled with gratitude. 
</P>
<P>
I would like all your readers to know that those young men from Camp Paige, 
among all the other firemen and firefighters, deserve special recognition and a 
"Thank you" bigger than any of us can describe for their extraordinary effort 
and determination. 
</P>
<P>
JAMES E. AHRENS 
</P>
<P>
Hacienda Heights 
</P>
</TEXT>
