<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEEN'S DEATH TIED TO HIT-RUN DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of an unidentified Latino teen-ager was found Saturday morning near 
Oceanside, apparently the victim of a hit-and-run driver. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said the victim, described only as a Juan Doe who appeared to have 
been an undocumented alien, was found in the center divider of Interstate 5, 
about two miles south of the San Onofre checkpoint. 
</P>
<P>
Kathy Gill, a California Highway Patrol spokeswoman, said the man had been dead 
four to eight hours. He was discovered about 7:15 a.m. by a passing motorist. 
No arrests have been made in the case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
