<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 45 people were killed in a 24-hour period in some of Sri Lanka's worst 
political violence, official sources said in Colombo. The sources blamed an 
extremist Sinhalese group for 35 deaths in Sinhalese-populated southern areas. 
Six people died in clashes in the Tamil-populated north and east, where Indian 
troops are fighting Tamil separatists. Chiefs of the three armed services and 
the police, responding to a threat to kill their families if they do not resign 
and help set up a socialist government, said soldiers and police will do their 
duty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
