<P>
Fleas carrying bubonic plague have been found on squirrels at two campgrounds 
in the San Jacinto Mountains near Idyllwild, said Riverside County health 
officials. James Lang, public health entomologist for the county health 
department, warned campers and hikers not to feed, touch or even get close to 
squirrels in the area. The two campgrounds where 10 squirrels tested positive 
for the plague-carrying fleas during the last two months were Boulder Basin and 
Stone Creek. Boulder Basin is about six miles north of Idyllwild and Stone 
Creek is four miles north of the mountain town. Symptoms of the disease are a 
reddening of the area around a flea bite, followed by flu-like symptoms. The 
plague can be treated with antibiotics if diagnosed early. 
