<TEXT>
<P>
Pacesetter Homes Inc., Newport Beach, reported a profit of $7,000 for the 
second quarter, contrasted with a loss of $771,000 for the period last year. 
Revenue increased 56% to $13.5 million from $8.6 million. For the first half of 
1989, net income totaled $219,000, contrasted with a loss of $321,000 for the 
first six months of 1988. Revenue declined 12% to $23.4 million from $26.7 
million. During the second quarter of 1989, the company provided a reserve for 
estimated tax audit assessments related to 1983 and 1984. This reserve reduced 
after-tax earnings by $640,000. 
</P>
